Greek Airports’ January Arrivals From Abroad 3.8% Up on Year Ago

-- B y   N a t a l i e   W e e k s
-- 
2011-02-16T09:46:10Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-16/greek-airports-january-arrivals-from-abroad-3-8-up-on-year-ago.html
International arrivals at Greek
airports rose 3.8 percent last month compared with January 2010,
according to data collected from five airports, including the
two biggest, by the  Association of Greek Tourism Enterprises .  Passenger arrivals from abroad increased to 229,392, from
221,047 in the year-earlier month, the association said in a
statement posted on its website.  Athens International Airport,  Greece ’s biggest, saw a 4
percent increase in international arrivals, to 165,789. Airports
of popular tourist spots such as Rhodes and Herakleion, on the
island of Crete, also experienced a rise.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Natalie Weeks in Athens at 
 nweeks2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Angela Cullen at 
